                    <span>The book gives you straight answers on how to face challenges, financial and otherwise, that come your way in life: on the job and at home. I liked the examples the authors used; they were vivid and real.  Bottom line is  solve the problems you face and take responsibility for your  actions.<p>Recommend this book in conjunction with another book on self  direction and leadership I use called:  "The Leader's Guide: 15  Essential Skills."</span>
                  
              
